rComments: As a seminar prof, Prof Esonwanne didn't lecture too much as students often took over. When he did speak however, it was always really interesting and insightful. He created a comfortable classroom environment for participation and marked fairly.

-Excellent course material -Great in-class discussions; participate & you'll really enjoy them -Very low workload; no essays, only a midterm and a final -Reading is moderate, but less than other English novel courses -Attendance IS mandatory, but you get basically everything out of the class by showing up -Professor is obviously very well-prepared
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Participation matters', 'Graded by few things']
